---
// The four isolation models, selectable per mount.
---

<figure>
	<svg class="gb-diagram" viewBox="0 0 720 250" role="img" aria-labelledby="dg-iso-title dg-iso-desc">
		<title id="dg-iso-title">Four tenant isolation models</title>
		<desc id="dg-iso-desc">
			Four panels. Shared RLS: one database where rows of different tenants live together, filtered by
			row-level security. Schema per tenant: one database with a private schema per tenant. Database per
			tenant: a dedicated database per tenant. Tenant-owned: the tenant's own external database joined
			through an encrypted mount.
		</desc>

		<rect class="d-box" x="16" y="20" width="158" height="150" rx="12" />
		<text class="d-label" x="95" y="46" text-anchor="middle">shared_rls</text>
		<rect class="d-chip" x="34" y="62" width="122" height="20" rx="5" />
		<circle class="d-node" cx="46" cy="72" r="4" /><text class="d-faint" x="58" y="76">tenant A rows</text>
		<rect class="d-chip" x="34" y="88" width="122" height="20" rx="5" />
		<circle cx="46" cy="98" r="4" fill="#7dd3fc" /><text class="d-faint" x="58" y="102">tenant B rows</text>
		<rect class="d-chip" x="34" y="114" width="122" height="20" rx="5" />
		<circle cx="46" cy="124" r="4" fill="#f472b6" /><text class="d-faint" x="58" y="128">tenant C rows</text>
		<text class="d-faint" x="95" y="158" text-anchor="middle">RLS filters every query</text>

		<rect class="d-box" x="192" y="20" width="158" height="150" rx="12" />
		<text class="d-label" x="271" y="46" text-anchor="middle">schema_per_tenant</text>
		<rect class="d-chip" x="210" y="62" width="122" height="34" rx="5" />
		<text class="d-faint" x="271" y="82" text-anchor="middle">schema tenant_a</text>
		<rect class="d-chip" x="210" y="104" width="122" height="34" rx="5" />
		<text class="d-faint" x="271" y="124" text-anchor="middle">schema tenant_b</text>
		<text class="d-faint" x="271" y="158" text-anchor="middle">one DB, private schemas</text>

		<rect class="d-box" x="368" y="20" width="158" height="150" rx="12" />
		<text class="d-label" x="447" y="46" text-anchor="middle">db_per_tenant</text>
		<rect class="d-chip d-box--accent" x="386" y="62" width="122" height="34" rx="5" />
		<text class="d-faint" x="447" y="82" text-anchor="middle">database A</text>
		<rect class="d-chip d-box--accent" x="386" y="104" width="122" height="34" rx="5" />
		<text class="d-faint" x="447" y="124" text-anchor="middle">database B</text>
		<text class="d-faint" x="447" y="158" text-anchor="middle">hardest walls</text>

		<rect class="d-box" x="544" y="20" width="158" height="150" rx="12" />
		<text class="d-label" x="623" y="46" text-anchor="middle">tenant_owned</text>
		<rect class="d-chip d-box--rust" x="562" y="62" width="122" height="48" rx="5" />
		<text class="d-faint" x="623" y="82" text-anchor="middle">your database</text>
		<text class="d-faint" x="623" y="98" text-anchor="middle">your DSN</text>
		<text class="d-faint" x="623" y="134" text-anchor="middle">🔒 AES-256-GCM mount</text>
		<text class="d-faint" x="623" y="158" text-anchor="middle">bring your own DB</text>

		<text class="d-faint" x="360" y="206" text-anchor="middle">← cheapest, densest</text>
		<path class="d-ring" d="M70 216H650" />
		<text class="d-faint" x="360" y="240" text-anchor="middle">hardest isolation →</text>
	</svg>
	<figcaption class="gb-diagram-note">
		Isolation is a per-mount choice, not a platform rebuild — one deployment can serve all four models at once.
	</figcaption>
</figure>
